node.text: The team won’t forget our time with our Norther neighbors — thank you Canada! Now we’re back in the states, and heading to the airshow in Owensboro, Kentucky, this weekend Aug. 14-15th!

node.text: Tech. Sgt. Lenny Buscemi was a motivating force on the F-22 Demo Team, his enthusiasm, professionalism and caring nature will be missed. Best of luck on your new assignment TSgt. Buscemi!

node.text:
The Team won’t forget this year’s Battle Creek Airshow any time soon! 
•
Also, we’ve arrived and are ready to show what Airpower means this Saturday & Sunday at about 2:15 p.m. at the Geneseo Airshow, NY!

node.text: Senior Airman Lauren Ooghe is one of the team’s avionics specialists, and during the airshow last week last week in her home state of Pennsylvania she had the unique experience of showing her mother what she does for the team and the U.S. Air Force. Avionics specialists like Ooghe are crucial to ensuring aircraft like the F-22 Raptor are mission ready by maintaining all flight computers, integrated avionics, and a multitude of electrical systems and components.

node.text: The team won’t forget our time with our Norther neighbors — thank you Canada! Now we’re back in the states, and heading to the airshow in Owensboro, Kentucky, this weekend Aug. 14-15th!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by F-22 Raptor Demo Team on August 09, 2021. May be an image of airplane and outdoors.

node.text: O Canada 🇨🇦! Thank you for the amazing airshow @abbyairshow — Being surrounded by such kind-hearted people and beautiful mountain vistas was an experience our team will never forget.

node.text: We had a great time at the @oregonairshow and we can’t wait for the @abbyairshow starting tomorrow!

node.text: Tech. Sgt. Lenny Buscemi was a motivating force on the F-22 Demo Team, his enthusiasm, professionalism and caring nature will be missed. Best of luck on your new assignment TSgt. Buscemi!

node.text: Thanks for a fantastic show Geneseo! And special thanks to the C-47 crew of Whiskey 7 for the once-in-a-lifetime ride. Whiskey 7 led the second wave on D-Day, and crossing the same troop door threshold where so many of America’s bravest took their last step was so humbling. Thank you @nationalwarplanemuseum 🇺🇸

node.text:
The Team won’t forget this year’s Battle Creek Airshow any time soon! 
•
Also, we’ve arrived and are ready to show what Airpower means this Saturday & Sunday at about 2:15 p.m. at the Geneseo Airshow, NY!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by F-22 Raptor Demo Team on July 05, 2021. May be an image of standing, fireworks and text.

node.text: The Battle Creek Airshow was phenomenal! A carnival, hot air balloons, fireworks, live music, and a killer airshow… What a way to spend American’s birthday. Next stop Geneseo, New York!
